Definition:
Linked Data is the engine of the Semantic Web, a term used by World Wide Web creator Sir Tim Berners-Lee to describe a future "Web of Data," wherein the Web will be organized via interlinking, interoperable data instead of collections of pages. Linked data is structured ontologically, with standard vocabularies and unique identifiers, so that it can be queried, added to, and repurposed by any machine or human language. Example: GeoNames has a Linked Data ontology.
